body:
# wanikani

Provides access to [wanikani](https://www.wanikani.com)'s [API](https://www.wanikani.com/api) in Crystal.

## Installation

Add this to your application's `shard.yml`:

```yaml
dependencies:
  wanikani:
    github: asterite/wanikani
```

## Usage

```crystal
require "wanikani"

api = Wanikani::API.new "your_api_key"

# Get user information
api.user_information

# Get radicals up to your level
api.radicals

# Get radicals up to a given level
api.radicals()

# Get radicals from multiple levels
api.radicals("1,3")

# And other similar methods...
```

## Contributing

1. Fork it ( https://github.com/asterite/wanikani/fork )
2. Create your feature branch (git checkout -b my-new-feature)
3. Commit your changes (git commit -am 'Add some feature')
4. Push to the branch (git push origin my-new-feature)
5. Create a new Pull Request

## Contributors

- [asterite](https://github.com/asterite) Ary Borenszweig - creator, maintainer

types.name: Wanikani
types.doc:
Provides access to [wanikani](https://www.wanikani.com)'s [API](https://www.wanikani.com/api):

- `Wanikani::API` is the main entry for the API
- `Wanikani::UserInformation`, `Wanikani::StudyQueue`, etc., are models returns from the API
- `Wanikani::API::Error` is returned in case of an error (wrong level passed, or invalid API key)
types.summary: Provides access to wanikani's API:

constructors.doc: Creates a new API with the given key.

def.name: vocabulary
def.body:
path = level_path("vocabulary", level)
if level
  get(path, Array(Vocabulary))
else
  get(path, General(Array(Vocabulary)))
end

types.name: Error
types.doc:
Raises in case of an API error: either an invalid API key, or invalid
levels argument to some of the methods (radicals, kanji and vocabulary).

def.body:
json.object do
  _type = @type
  if _type.nil?
  else
    json.field("type") do
      _type.to_json(json)
    end
  end
  _character = @character
  if _character.nil?
  else
    json.field("character") do
      _character.to_json(json)
    end
  end
  _kana = @kana
  if _kana.nil?
  else
    json.field("kana") do
      _kana.to_json(json)
    end
  end
  _meaning = @meaning
  if _meaning.nil?
  else
    json.field("meaning") do
      _meaning.to_json(json)
    end
  end
  _level = @level
  if _level.nil?
  else
    json.field("level") do
      _level.to_json(json)
    end
  end
  _percentage = @percentage
  if _percentage.nil?
  else
    json.field("percentage") do
      if _percentage
        StringToInt32Converter.to_json(_percentage, json)
      else
        nil.to_json(json)
      end
    end
  end
end
